text: Hohenfels (literally High Cliffs) is a municipality in Neumarkt in Upper Palatinate () in Bavaria, Germany. The town is home to the United States Army Garrison Hohenfels, which operates the Joint Multinational Readiness Center for training NATO armed forces. ==Related pages== *Grafenwöhr ==References== == Other websites == * U.S. Army Garrison Bavaria—the consolidated official site for the U.S. Army in Bavaria Category:Neumarkt (district)
title: Hohenfels, Bavaria
